<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bit" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bit,</orth> 1) the iron part of a bridle which is put in the mouth of the horse: <cit><quote>the iron b. he crusheth 'tween his teeth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 269" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 269</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 3, 23</bibl>.<lb />2) morsel: <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.133" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 2, 159</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.8.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 8, 20</bibl> (Q <emph>bait,</emph> F<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>bed</emph>). <bibl n="shak. cor 4.5.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 5, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 174</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>